<subSubSection id="CE8219F3FFD75860FF23F911FD66F889" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="86274A78FFD75860FF23F911FD66F889" blockId="22.[151,1436,1663,1832]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="B4EC966AFFD75860FF23F911FE96F936" bold="true" box="[151,267,1664,1688]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
Not a new record. Mak’s tentative identification is accompanied by a rather short diagnosis. Since 
<number id="3050585FFFD75860FAD0F9EEFA01F939" box="[1380,1436,1663,1687]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="1982.0">1982</number>
several new species of 
<taxonomicName id="419831FBFFD75860FE15F935FDA5F912" box="[417,568,1700,1724]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Metavermilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B4EC966AFFD75860FE15F935FDA5F912" box="[417,568,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Metavermilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been described, see overview in 
<bibRefCitation id="E2093789FFD75860FC41F935FB51F912" box="[1013,1228,1700,1724]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Nishi, E., Kupriyanova, E. &amp; Tachikawa, H. (2007) Metavermilia ogasawaraensis sp. nov. (Serpulidae: Sabellida: Polychaeta: Annelida) from deep-sea locations off Ogasawara Island, Japan with a literature overview of the genus. Zootaxa, 1447, 47 - 56." type="journal article">
Nishi 
<emphasis id="B4EC966AFFD75860FB8FF934FBE8F912" box="[1083,1141,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number id="3050585FFFD75860FB32F935FB59F912" box="[1158,1220,1700,1724]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" value="2007.0">2007</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. As mentioned by Mak, the yellowish horny distal cap of the operculum is unlike 
<taxonomicName id="419831FBFFD75860FCC4F958FC7DF94E" box="[880,992,1736,1760]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Metavermilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="inflata">
<emphasis id="B4EC966AFFD75860FCC4F958FC7DF94E" box="[880,992,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. inflata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and in the light of present knowledge might indicate that he had a juvenile specimen of 
<taxonomicName id="419831FBFFD75860FD73F97CFC73F8AA" authority="Sun, 1998" authorityName="Sun" authorityYear="1998" box="[711,1006,1772,1796]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Metavermilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="nanshaensis">
<emphasis id="B4EC966AFFD75860FD73F97CFCE8F8AA" box="[711,885,1772,1796]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">M. nanshaensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E2093789FFD75860FCC8F97DFC73F8AA" author="Sun" box="[892,1006,1772,1796]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refString="Sun, R. P. (1998) The Polynoidae, Eunicidae and Serpulidae (Annelida: Polychaeta) from Nansha Islands and adjacent waters. In: The Multidisciplinary Oceanographic Expedition Team of Academia Sinica to Nansha (eds.), Studies on marine fauna and flora and biogeography of the Nansha Islands and neighbouring waters. III. Contribution 2942 from the Institute of Oceanology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, 79 - 114." type="journal article" year="1998">
Sun, 
<quantity id="4160E79DFFD75860FC02F97DFC73F8AA" box="[950,1006,1772,1796]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.07492" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="in" value="1998.0">1998</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in hand. More material and a description of the tube are needed for a reliable identification.
</paragraph>
